  "body": "# SOLVED\r\n\r\n### Sorry about the panic.\r\n\r\nIt all started here: https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/2077#issuecomment-490027735\r\n\r\nHave to pass string.\r\n\r\nSo I’ve added `toWei` and `fromWei` helper methods.\r\n\r\n`web3.eth.geBalance` returns a string so because I had helpers already I used `fromWei` to have human-readable numbers.\r\n\r\nThat was a mistake.\r\n\r\nPreviously my workflow with BigNumbers involved `toString()` and then `parseInt()` to workaround error of losing precision.\r\n\r\n_(NOTE: I’m OK with losing precision, very often there is a gas fee, I use `closeTo` syntax)_\r\n\r\nPreviously `parseInt` on giagantic strings with loads of zeros was just fine. In the human readable work, `parseInt(99.5)` was a disaster that cost me pretty much effectively the whole day of scratching my head.\r\n\r\n---  \r\n\r\nI was so sure about myself.\r\n\r\nSo many things do not work all the time, that I was pretty sure it’s them who are wrong, not me.\r\n",
